n><hr size=1> Alecto appeared sitting above the layout of Tartarus, she being the only Furie able to go into the Underworld by free will, decided to look in that area. She sighed finding nothing at the moment.<br>
<br>
Megaera immediatly went to Olympus as well as the lost areas where the living Titans were rumored to roam. She of course found nothing as well.<br>
<br>
Tisiphone was a bit smarter than her sisters, she took the form of a Mermaid and went into the seas looking for the Tridents whereabouts. <br>
<br>
When the sisters would find it. . . .was unknown to many. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/30/01 3:12:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Searching for a Stolen Trident</span><hr size=1> ::Hades sat on his Obsidian throne, sitting as still as a statue, slumped slightly.  Sensing Alecto scouring about in his realm he sat up straight and closed his eyes.  He touched the tips of his fingers to themselves and seemed to go into an almost meditative state.  After a few minutes he reopened his eyes.  He then closed them again.  Suddenly Alecto heard Hades' voice in her head::<br>
<br>
&quot;Alecto, the Trident is not down here.  If it was in my Realm, believe me, I would know it.  As Lord of this Realm, I know all that enter and leave here.  You waste your time scouring here.&quot;  <br>
<br>
::Hades then opened his eyes and sat a bit more relaxed in his Throne.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/utheerinyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Erinyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/30/01 11:52:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> Alecto almost growled as she vanished from the top of Tartarus and appeared before Hades.<br>
<br>
&quot;Each of my sisters took an area to look over. Let's just say this was all that was left. Tisiphone went into the waters. No immortal would ever try to test her, if she begins to speak, he may flee to either Tartarus or Olympus. Megaera is at Olympus. I'm just stuck here you could say.&quot;<br>
<br>
She then proped herself up on the arm of his throne.<br>
<br>
&quot;So how's Persephone?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/30/01 7:36:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: </span><hr size=1> ::Hades looks at Alecto and smiles::  Persephone as far as I know is doing fine.  She's wandering about somewhere, ::Nods his head up:: somewhere topside.  The trident is not here, though if it will make you feel better you are more than welcome to continue your search.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/1/01 3:42:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=pos006 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Searching for a Stollen Trident</span><hr size=1> ::Poseidon calls in his heralds to the living room.::<br>
<br>
&quot;My servants go to Lord Hades in Tartarus and bid him tell you how the search is going. Tell him the sisters are taking too long and my trident should have been found by now.&quot;<br>
<br>
::His servants bowed in reverence and immediatly set off for tartarus in a bronze chariot pulled by 2 white stallions. When the heralds reached the castle of Hades they got off the chariot and walked into the palace to the throne of Hades. Bowing before the lord of darkness the 2 heralds told Hades what Poseidon had bid them say. Staying on their knees with their heads bowed the servants awaited an answer.::  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/2/01 4:28:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A Response</span><hr size=1> ::Hades sat on his Obsidian throne with his fingertips touching one another.  He looked sternly at the heralds for a moment as they layed still bowed in their obedience::<br>
<br>
&quot;I bid ye to rise.&quot;  ::He said with a dark voice.  He then looked them all dead in the eyes once  they stood::<br>
<br>
&quot;Tell my brother that more patience is required on his part.  The Furies are currently searching out for the stolen trident.  Olympus, the Sea, and here in Tartarus.  As soon as I hear anything I will inform him further.  For now I have heard nothing.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He then waves his hand bidding the heralds to leave and return to their master, Poseidon:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/2/01 10:19:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=pos006 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: News</span><hr size=1> ::Poseidon watches as his servants enter his palace and then they come to him with the news. As the lord of the sea drinks his nectar he listens to what the heralds report.::<br>
<br>
&quot;I see, too bad the furies cannot be as fast as the messenger god Hermes. My greatest possession would have been found already. Okay you two may be off.&quot;<br>
<br>
::Poseidon waves his hand and the two heralds leave the palace.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/5/01 4:10:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> On my own</span><hr size=1> ::Poseidon appears in the throne room of Hades and walks toward his brother. He stops before the throne of Hades and bows slightly. ::<br>
<br>
&quot;My brother, since the furies have now refused to do what they said they would do I will get my trident myself. I told them that the river god had it and he would be in his abode and that would be where they could find him. I will go there myself and retrieve it. Brother, I thank you for your help but you can leave this business of mine alone now. I shall have no more trouble in getting it.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/5/01 4:51:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: On my own</span><hr size=1> ::Hades nodded slightly to his brother and then cleared his throat::<br>
<br>
&quot;Then go forth and enact the justice of Olympus on his head.  And should you still decide to bring the River god before to be 'detained' here, you are still welcome.  Its been a while since an Immortal has come here to stay on a 'permanent' basis.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He then smirks:: &quot;I need a new pool boy anyway.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/5/01 6:04:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=pos006 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Searching for a Stollen Trident</span><hr size=1> &quot;That I shall do brother, and you shall have that pool boy soon. I will bring him here in shackles.&quot;<br>
<br>
::Poseidon vanishes in a flash of bright blue light.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/14/01 9:47:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=pos006 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Searching for a Stollen Trident</span><hr size=1> ::Poseidon appears in Hades sweat glistening on his near naked body. He wears a pair of golden sandles and a loin cloth made from sheep skin. He has an adamantine chain wrapped about his left hand and behind him shackled on both his feet and hands with adamantine cuffs stands the bruised and beaten River god, Asopus. In his right hand glows his golden trident, found at last. He tugs hard at Asopus, who tumbles to the floor before the throne of Hades. Poseidon looks into his brothers eyes.::<br>
<br>
&quot;My brother, the criminal has been apprehended and now awaits his punishment.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/15/01 4:09:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Punishment...</span><hr size=1> ::Hades sat patiently at his throne, very regally and upright.  He glared at the beaten river god.  His shadowed eyes flashed with a purple light for a brief moment::<br>
<br>
&quot;Ah...my pool-boy has arrived.  Leave me brother if you wish.  If not...stay and watch.&quot;<br>
<br>
::Hades then stood up from his throne.  And walked very slowly and methodically to Asopus.  He grabbed him by the back of his hair and yanked his head back.  Hades then with what seemed with little effort threw him face first into the wall on the other side of the room.  He then took his time approaching him.  He yanked on his chain pulling him off the wall.  He then looked up at one of the beams across his throne room.  He grabbed the loose end of the long chain and threw it over the beam.  He then pulled the loose chain to the ground, leaving Asopus hanging in the air.  He then dropped him, having him hit the ground::<br>
<br>
::He then walks over to his throne.  He grabs one of three amphora's on a table beside his throne.  He walks over the river god and forces him to drink from the Amphora.  The River God suddenly becomes very lethargic and tired.  Hades then yanks on the chain, suspending Asopus in the air again.  He then drives a pike into the ground on the chain.  Hades smirked as the lethargic River God swayed slightly, suspended from beam::<br>
<br>
&quot;That which I fed you was water from the River Lethe.  You will not even have the urge to fight or even squirm out of this.  Now, I will leave you hanging here until I think of a worse fate for you.  Which could take till Doomsday.  Or better yet...perhaps I shall let the Furies have their way with you.  That is assuming they are not still on strike.  I know they would take great pleasure in punishing one such as you.  Oh well, their loss if they choose not to.  Just more fun for me.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He then sat down on his throne and watched the river-god dangle like a prized caught fish:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/16/01 10:17:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=pos006 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Searching for a Stollen Trident</span><hr size=1> ::Poseidon looks at Hades and his punishment beginning to be carried out on the river god. He smiles and holds his trident with both his hands in front of his chest.::<br>
<br>
&quot;Good job brother. Enjoy your water boy. He's  got a warrenty for eternity.&quot;<br>
<br>
::Poseidon turns around and begins to walk away and as he walks he disappears in a flash of blue light. His last words linger in the air like an echo.::<br>
<br>
&quot;Another time brother.&quot; <p>Poseidon</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A> at: 6/16/01 11:35:20 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFF33>- </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite>Amazons Unite</a><font color=#FFFF33> - </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23>The Olympian Gods</a> <font color=#FFFF33> - </font><a href="http://www.amazonsunite.i-p.com">Home</a><font color=#FFFF33> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.3 b4<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  